DA Gerald Fox appeared for the State.  Defendant appeared in person and with Attorney Frederickson. No victim interest, per State.  Defendant plead no contest to the charge.  Joint recommendation for 12 months probation, concurrent with probation now serving.  Court recited the charge and possible penalties on the count he plead to.  Defendant understood.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the pleas.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the pleas.  Found guilty of possession of drug paraphernalia, contrary to 961.573(1) as a repeater 939.62(1)(a).  Joint recommendation for 1 year probation.    The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by a risk and needs assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.  Test for drugs.   No contact with David Barhyte or Mary Fisher.
